<paragraph id="8B257F639ECC72CAC38AF0AAA99736F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Scattered to gregarious on leaf litter in mixed forest dominated with broadleaf trees, in summer.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="176FB8E40245B95A593B0E9A8AD98CDA" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EB652E6C1C0BD2DEF11AFCB60481B040" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="02280C1150A9607AC41448AC195063E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">The Republic of Korea.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="552BF0D71C6F3E0AC93B126D80E47EB0" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="4A55ED516C3E29093F10C5157865D0EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="234F71B6B786240F4CED70B7CDC3CDDE" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="2E5E6286A46B16BB4199B676EDE6A7C9" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis undulata" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis id="6AF518135BCA4CB438C192510A19110D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="7BDBFEFBA45C5201836CBABAC75FA4A3" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. subpruinosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="subpruinosa">
<emphasis id="E56DA34D96240710E31636FB8B3667D4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. subpruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Murrill) R.H. Petersen. 
<taxonomicName id="069B776587A853914DF80F3D33B9FF4F" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis subpruinosa" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="subpruinosa">
<emphasis id="EC5532BB014CF9A9B8F2FEF2C84760A7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis subpruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has differences in having small central papilla on pileus, fewer lamellulae (3-4 series), vivid colored lamellae, thicker basidiospores (4.5-5.2 
<normalizedToken id="E9A103D391870DE5EA444530F62D8326" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide), larger basidia (30-36 
<normalizedToken id="50CF4552951B5B585916DCDF3D66018E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7.5-8.5 
<normalizedToken id="4FB3BBBEA1069F70FCB765F7DBE79C37" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and cheilocystidia (25-80 
<normalizedToken id="8686D0657C7C083D5F7FC4ADEABC6478" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-16 
<normalizedToken id="ABFCADA4808A79AF0BEE15C7524D01C4" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), thick-walled trama hyphae (0.5-1 
<normalizedToken id="32FB745582A4CB3B60F8D1BE66835DBB" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), caulocystidia with a wider size range, and a habit of growing solitary on rotten twigs or logs (
<bibRefCitation id="8D642F23C3765D5F33A19CAF8EFD6B8C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="166 - 176" refId="B10" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Hemmes, DE, 1999. Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus. Mycologia 91 (1): 166 - 176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" title="Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" volume="91" year="1999">Desjardin et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="6E6F51DA5638DEAAD71FE1055906AD92" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis undulata" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis id="2F0224BC925DCBE763B47FE21007816A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName id="617A8730937B4BD84156CCAB36E0306F" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. villosipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="villosipes">
<emphasis id="517505F2D5179B8365FA2B2F0003D0F5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. villosipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<taxonomicName id="0EFD243B2F57926C28A81F53FC50C810" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. villosipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="villosipes">
<emphasis id="DBE61B16B9DFDB2371B72619A7188232" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. villosipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated by having fewer lamelluale (2-3 series), vivid colored lamellae, thicker stipe (1.5-4.0 mm), slightly thicker basidiospores (3.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken id="C225F519BA1772526FB3C94698D455E5" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide), and basidia (25-34 
<normalizedToken id="2573445BDE0B63A07DF496BB760FA2AA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6.5-7.5 
<normalizedToken id="5A8EB3410BEE7A5A0569474F5BD7BC69" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="946B9D83AA0E88FCFD20CCD18A5B1E78" author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="141 - 148" refId="B9" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Perry, BA, 1997. Gymnopus villosipes -a common collybioid agaric from California. Mycotaxon 64: 141 - 148" title="Gymnopus villosipes - a common collybioid agaric from California." volume="64" year="1997">Desjardin et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
